undergraduate options in biomedical informatics stanford medicine stanford school of medicine biomedical informatics search this site only stanford medical sites ways to give find a person alumni lane library ways to give find a person biomedical informatics undergraduate educational options the biomedical informatics program does not offer an undergraduate major directly for students interested in an undergraduate major in with an option to specialize in biomedical informatics see the biomedical computation major however stanford undergraduates may choose to combine their undergraduate major with the co terminal masters degree the biomedical informatics co terminal ms may be combined with many undergraduate majors however computer science any of the biological science programs or the biomedical computation major offer the most efficient combination of the two degrees undergraduates may apply to the co terminal program upon completion of 120 units but no later than the quarter preceding the completion of an undergraduate degree please consult the bulletin for details about coterminal programs you may also contact any of the members of the biomedical informatics executive committee who can either answer questions about the program or advise you on the application procedure the complete description of the biomedical informatics co terminal program requirements and other details may be found in this website under prospective students graduate degrees masters co terminal ms see the left hand navigation bar you are here current tab 4 stanford medicine school of medicine biomedical informatics for stanford undergraduates navigation for this section prospective students overview graduate degrees dual degrees postdoctoral training distance education programs for medical students for stanford undergraduates for international applicants additional links bmi help looking for something search biomedical informatics help pages site navigation home about bmi overview our mission 